cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of hyper-parameters in a reinforcement learning algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of Bayesian optimization and Gaussian process regression, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) research. The paper also deals with control policies in uncertain environments, which is a topic of interest in systems and control (cs.SY) research. Finally, the use of bandits-based approach is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
